WEBVTT

00:02.166 --> 00:03.932
Hey, uh, who's
free tonight?

00:03.934 --> 00:05.667
- Oh, I think I'm...
- Hang on.

00:05.669 --> 00:06.935
We've made this
mistake before.

00:06.937 --> 00:08.470
It's how we
wound up at

00:08.472 --> 00:12.040
his cousin Deepak's
Tupperware party.

00:12.042 --> 00:13.942
Hey, you use that
collapsible bowl all the time,

00:13.943 --> 00:15.010
and you know it.

00:15.012 --> 00:16.478
And it's not
like that.

00:16.480 --> 00:19.815
I just thought we could, you
know, hang out and go to a bar.

00:19.817 --> 00:21.082
- Sure. - Very well.
- Sounds fun.

00:21.084 --> 00:22.818
And watch cricket.

00:23.754 --> 00:27.389
That sound you hear,
ironically, crickets.

00:28.859 --> 00:30.292
Hey, guys.

00:30.294 --> 00:31.493
Hey, Bert,
how you doing?

00:31.495 --> 00:32.994
Well, you know, we geologists

00:32.996 --> 00:35.964
always get a little sad
when Rocktober's over.

00:36.700 --> 00:38.900
- Wordplay?
- Yes.

00:38.902 --> 00:39.868
Funny wordplay?

00:39.870 --> 00:41.436
- What do you think?
- Eh.

00:41.438 --> 00:44.706
Trust your gut.

00:44.708 --> 00:45.841
Sheldon, I've got these

00:45.843 --> 00:47.442
four-billion-year-old
meteorites.

00:47.444 --> 00:51.046
I thought maybe they'd show
signs of neutrino interactions.

00:51.048 --> 00:53.782
I could really use someone like
you to help me with the math.

00:53.784 --> 00:58.553
Oh, so they would act as
natural dark matter detectors.

00:58.555 --> 00:59.654
That sounds interesting.

00:59.656 --> 01:02.457
It does, but it's still geology.

01:03.927 --> 01:06.595
Sorry, Bert, I don't have time
to play rocks with you.

01:06.597 --> 01:08.129
I'm not asking you
to play rocks.

01:08.131 --> 01:10.499
I'm asking you to collaborate
on a research project.

01:10.501 --> 01:11.466
Although, if
there's time,

01:11.468 --> 01:13.134
I guess we could play a round

01:13.136 --> 01:15.537
of zinc, zinc, piece of quartz.

01:16.673 --> 01:18.807
Does sound better
than cricket.

01:20.444 --> 01:21.543
Thank you for asking.

01:21.545 --> 01:23.645
Unfortunately, I have
real science to do.

01:23.647 --> 01:25.514
But you feel free
to rock on.

01:25.516 --> 01:27.782
That's how you do it.

01:27.784 --> 01:29.651
All right.

01:29.653 --> 01:30.685
Sheldon, what are you doing?

01:30.687 --> 01:32.420
Bert's one of
the top guys in his field.

01:32.422 --> 01:36.691
And somewhere there's a mime
who's top in his field,

01:36.693 --> 01:38.994
but you don't see me rushing
to collaborate with him

01:38.996 --> 01:42.397
on new ways to be
stuck in a box.

01:42.399 --> 01:46.568
Also something I would
watch instead of cricket.

01:48.000 --> 01:54.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:57.214 --> 01:58.213
Oh. (chuckles)

01:58.215 --> 01:59.514
Hello.

01:59.516 --> 02:01.216
Hey, Sheldon.

02:01.218 --> 02:04.286
I've been thinking
about it, and I suppose

02:04.288 --> 02:07.355
I-I could help you
with your research.

02:07.357 --> 02:08.556
What changed your mind?

02:08.559 --> 02:10.191
Bert, I'm a gift horse.

02:10.193 --> 02:12.260
Don't look me in the mouth.

02:12.262 --> 02:14.262
Sorry. I'm happy
you want to help out.

02:14.264 --> 02:16.932
If it's easier for you, we could
just work at your office.

02:16.934 --> 02:19.034
No, no, no,
not my office, no.

02:19.036 --> 02:20.869
Uh, let's-let's
do it here,

02:20.871 --> 02:24.839
in-in the evenings,
after everyone's gone home.

02:24.841 --> 02:27.542
I just have to see
if my evenings are free.

02:27.544 --> 02:29.844
That's a joke. They are.

02:29.846 --> 02:31.046
Okay.

02:31.048 --> 02:32.847
Well, then I will
see you tonight.

02:34.785 --> 02:36.017
(gasps)

02:36.019 --> 02:37.953
Well, you know what?

02:37.955 --> 02:40.655
(stammers) Close the blinds.
We can start right now.

02:42.125 --> 02:45.660
♪ Our whole universe
was in a hot, dense state ♪

02:45.662 --> 02:49.097
♪ Then nearly 14 billion years
ago expansion started... Wait! ♪

02:49.099 --> 02:50.732
♪ The Earth began to cool ♪

02:50.734 --> 02:53.268
♪ The autotrophs began to drool,
Neanderthals developed tools ♪

02:53.270 --> 02:55.937
♪ We built the Wall ♪
♪ <i>We built the pyramids</i> ♪

02:55.939 --> 02:58.607
♪ Math, Science, History,
unraveling the mystery ♪

02:58.609 --> 03:00.508
♪ That all started
with a big bang ♪

03:00.510 --> 03:00.685
♪ <i>Bang!</i> ♪

03:00.686 --> 03:04.686
<b><font color="#00FF00">♪ The Big Bang Theory 11x07 ♪</font></b>
<font color="#00FFFF">The Geology Methodology</font>
